name: Willow's Song
comments: Performed by the character "Willow", played by Britt Ekland. Ekland was dubbed (and, since she was pregnant, a body double was used for her naked scenes). According to the film's associate musical director Gary Carpenter, Ekland's singing on the film was voiced by Rachel Verney, and a further version, sung by Lesley Mackie, was recorded for The Wicker Man - The Original Soundtrack Album LP, eventually released in 2002. Other, unconfirmed sources credit the song to Annie Ross .
